[{"id":"VR440789","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a painting of a cityscape. A building is shown at the center of the painting. A row of buildings is shown on either side of the building at the center. A street is shown between the center building and each row of buildings. The building in the center of the painting is cylindrical, two stories high, and has columns wrapping around it on both stories. The buildings all sit on a flat surface of large square tiles decorated with geometric shapes.\" height=\"143\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR440789.g04.png\" width=\"500\" /><span class=\"mandatory_credit_line\">Galleria Nazionale delle Marche</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">In the work shown, the artist created the effect of spatial recession by using which of the following techniques?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR440789_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Continuous narrative</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Linear perspective</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Hierarchical scale</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Tenebrism</p>"],"answer":1}]